President Cyril Ramaphosa is said to be considering the nomination of a South African-born US-based luxury handbag designer, Lana Marks, to be the next United States Ambassador to South Africa. The nomination by President Donald Trump was submitted by the US State Department some weeks ago. Marks is currently based in Palm Beach, Florida. Click to find out more about the nominee: <a href="https://iono.fm/e/608549">Content hosted by iono.fm</a>